From the 243 flocks assayed using RT-PCR, a total of 39 tested positive for IBV (16.05%) (Fig. 1B). Of the 39 isolates sequenced, it was possible to determine the genotypes of 32 (82.05%) using BLAST (Table 2
). A total of five genotypes were represented within the sample size. The majority of samples showed greatest homology to genotype 793/B (n = 26/39; 66.67%), with the remaining isolates relating closely to M41 (n = 2/39; 5.12%), D274 (n = 2/39; 5.12%), IS/1494/06 (n = 1/39; 2.56%) and IS/885/00 (n = 1/39; 2.56%). All 32 sequenced samples were submitted to GenBank and assigned accession numbers (Fig. 2
).
